erfere with or disrupt the proper operation of the Marketplace or the servers, networks, or infrastructure used to make the Marketplace available, or violating any requirements, procedures, policies, or regulations of such networks or infrastructure, including, but not limited to, transmitting viruses, worms, or other malicious code, or engaging in denial-of-service attacks.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Violation of Applicable Laws, Regulations, and Third-Party Rights:</strong> Violating any applicable international, federal, state, or local laws, statutes, ordinances, regulations, administrative rules, or legally binding directives, or infringing, misappropriating, or violating any third-party rights, including, but not limited to, intellectual property rights, privacy rights, contractual rights, or proprietary rights.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Circumvention and Manipulation of Automated Systems and AI Functionalities:</strong> Attempting to circumvent, bypass, manipulate, or otherwise interfere with automated systems and processes implemented by the Marketplace, including, but not limited to, content moderation tools, fraud detection mechanisms, sanctions screening systems, and AI-driven functionalities and APIs integrated into the Marketplace. Users are strictly prohibited from engaging in any activities intended to generate false positives or negatives in automated content moderation systems, or otherwise interfere with the intended functioning of AI-driven features and APIs integrated into the Marketplace, including, but not limited to, reverse engineering or any other methods aimed at circumventing or manipulating such functionalities, or attempting to gain unauthorized or disproportionate benefits from such systems through manipulation or circumvention.<br>Violation of these guidelines may result in account suspension, termination, or legal action.</p><h3><strong>2.3. Compliance with Laws</strong></h3><p>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <