sp; &nbsp; <strong>Unwavering Commitment to Sanctions and Export Control Compliance:</strong> TrekGuider Inc. unequivocally commits to conducting all business operations with unwavering adherence to, and full compliance with, all applicable sanctions, export controls, and trade embargoes rigorously imposed, administered, and enforced by the United States government and other relevant jurisdictions worldwide. This paramount commitment encompasses, but is not limited to, strict and continuous adherence to all regulations, directives, and restrictions promulgated, administered, and enforced by the U.S. Office of Foreign Assets Control (OFAC) of the U.S. Department of the Treasury and the Bureau of Industry and Security (BIS) of the U.S. Department of Commerce, as these regulations may be amended, expanded, or superseded from time to time.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Absolute and Comprehensive Prohibition on Use by Sanctioned Parties and in Sanctioned Jurisdictions:</strong> Access to and utilization of the TrekGuider Marketplace is strictly, absolutely, and comprehensively prohibited for any and all individuals or entities who are, or who represent, warrant, or covenant that they are not, directly or indirectly:<br><br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Sanctioned Geographies:</strong> Located in, resident in, domiciled in, or a national, citizen, or government of, any comprehensively sanctioned, embargoed, or restricted country, territory, or jurisdiction, as designated, amended, or expanded from time to time by the U.S. government or other relevant sanctions authorities. This currently includes, but is not limited to, Cuba, Iran, North Korea, Syria, Venezuela, and the Crimea, Donetsk People\\\'s Republic, Luhansk People\\\'s Republic, Kherson and Zaporizhzhia regions of Ukraine, as these jurisdictions may be amended or expanded from time to time by the U.S. government.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Sanctioned Parties and Listed Entities:</strong> Specifically identified, designated, or listed on any U.S. government sanctions lists, restricted parties lists, denied persons lists, or entity lists, or any similar lists promulgated, maintained, or enforced by OFAC, BIS, or other U.S. government agencies, or by relevant international organizations or jurisdictions, that restrict, prohibit, or otherwise limit transactions, dealings, or interactions with listed parties. This prohibition includes, without limitation, identification on the OFAC Specially Designated Nationals and Blocked Persons List (SDN List), the BIS Denied Persons List, the BIS Entity List, the BIS Unverified List, and any other such lists, irrespective of their nomenclature or issuing authority.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Entities Controlled by Sanctioned Parties:</strong> Directly or indirectly owned or controlled, in the aggregate, by 50 percent or more, individually or in the aggregate, by one or more persons or entities identified in the categories above. This comprehensive prohibition explicitly extends to any and all entities owned or controlled, directly or indirectly, by sanctioned parties, irrespective of the entity\\\'s jurisdiction of incorporation, principal place of business, or operational activities.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Universal and Unqualified Prohibition of Sanctioned Transactions and Activities:</strong> You explicitly, unequivocally, and irrevocably agree, warrant, and covenant that you will not, under any circumstances, utilize the TrekGuider Marketplace, directly or indirectly, for any transactions, activities, or interactions that would, could, or might reasonably be construed to constitute a violation, circumvention, or evasion of U.S. sanctions laws, export control laws, or any other applicable regulations governing restricted, prohibited, or controlled transactions, activities, or destinations. This comprehensive, universal, and unqualified prohibition includes, but is not limited to, knowingly or unknowingly engaging in transactions or activities that involve, directly or indirectly:<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Sanctioned Individuals, Entities, and Jurisdictions:</strong> Transactions, dealings, or interactions with, on behalf of, or for the ultimate benefit of individuals or entities located in, resident in, domiciled in, nationals of, citizens of, or controlled by sanctioned countries, territories, or jurisdictions, or parties specifically identified, designated, or listed on U.S. government sanctions lists or restricted parties lists, as comprehensively delineated above.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Export-Controlled Products, Services, Software, or Technologies without Mandatory Licenses:</strong> The offer, sale, export, re-export, transfer, diversion, provision of access to, or facilitation of transactions involving any products, services, software, or technologies that are subject to U.S. export controls and require mandatory licenses, license exceptions, or other governmental authorizations for export, re-export, or in-country transfer to certain restricted or embargoed destinations, end-users, or for proscribed end-uses, without first meticulously obtaining, fully complying with, and maintaining in full force and effect, all required licenses, license exceptions, or other authorizations from the U.S. government and all other relevant authorities with competent jurisdiction. This comprehensive prohibition explicitly includes, but is not limited to, controlled digital products, encryption technologies, technical data, software, and any other controlled items or technologies.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Circumvention, Evasion, or Violation of Sanctions or Export Controls:</strong> Any activity, transaction, or interaction, whether direct or indirect, overt or covert, that has the express or implied purpose, intent, or reasonably foreseeable effect of evading, circumventing, violating, causing a violation of, or conspiring to violate any applicable U.S. sanctions, export control laws, or regulations, or that would, could, or might reasonably facilitate, enable, induce, or assist any other person or entity, whether affiliated or unaffiliated, to violate such laws and regulations.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Benefit to Sanctioned Jurisdictions or Parties or Diversion to Prohibited End-Uses:</strong> Any activity, transaction, or interaction that would, could, or might reasonably be construed to directly or indirectly benefit, finance, sponsor, support, or otherwise contribute to the economic, commercial, financial, industrial, military, or technological capabilities or interests of sanctioned countries, territories, individuals, or entities, or that could foreseeably result in the diversion of goods, services, or technology to prohibited end-uses or end-users in violation of applicable export control laws.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Proactive and Comprehensive Marketplace Monitoring, Screening, Interdiction, and Enforcement Measures:</strong> To proactively ensure rigorous, continuous, and demonstrable compliance with all applicable sanctions and export control laws, and to maintain the unimpeachable integrity of the Marketplace as a legally compliant and ethically operated platform, TrekGuider Inc. proactively implements, diligently maintains, and continuously enhances comprehensive, multi-layered, and technologically advanced monitoring, screening, interdiction, and enforcement measures, which include, but are not limited to:<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Automated, Real-Time, and Retrospective Sanctions Screening:</strong> Employing sophisticated, industry-leading automated sanctions screening systems, software platforms, and data analytics technologies to conduct continuous, real-time, and retrospective screening of users (particularly sellers and high-value buyers), transactions, user-generated content, and all other relevant data points against meticulously curated, dynamically updated, and exhaustive sanctions lists, restricted parties lists, denied persons lists, entity lists, and other relevant government watchlists and restricted jurisdiction lists, as promulgated and updated by OFAC, BIS, and other U.S. government agencies and relevant international authorities.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Automated and Manual Transaction Blocking, Rejection, Freezing, and Interdiction:</strong> Implementing robust, multi-layered, and continuously refined automated and manual controls, protocols, and procedures to systematically and effectively reject, block, freeze, interdict, prevent, and otherwise impede any and all transactions, activities, access attempts, or content uploads that are flagged, identified, or reasonably suspected as potentially violating sanctions or export control laws, or that involve, directly or indirectly, sanctioned parties, sanctioned jurisdictions, or transactions with prohibited destinations, end-users, or end-uses.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Immediate Account Suspension, Permanent Termination, and Access Restriction for Violations and Suspected Violations:</strong> Reserving the unequivocal, absolute, and non-reviewable right, exercisable in TrekGuider Inc.\'s sole and exclusive discretion, to immediately and without prior notice, explanation, or opportunity for remediation, suspend, temporarily disable, permanently terminate, or comprehensively restrict access to any and all accounts of users who are definitively determined to be in actual or suspected violation of these Sanctions and Export Control Compliance provisions, or who are reasonably suspected, in TrekGuider Inc.\'s sole and exclusive judgment, of engaging in activities that may constitute, facilitate, or enable a violation of applicable sanctions or export control laws, regulations, or directives.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Rigorous Internal Investigations, Comprehensive Audit Trails, and Mandatory Reporting to Authorities:</strong> Conducting prompt, thorough, and meticulously documented internal investigations of any and all suspected, alleged, or potential violations of sanctions or export control laws, regulations, or directives, and maintaining comprehensive audit trails and evidentiary records of all such investigations and related compliance activities. Where legally mandated, ethically advisable, or deemed reasonably necessary or appropriate in TrekGuider Inc.\'s sole and exclusive judgment, proactively and voluntarily reporting suspected violations, confirmed violations, and other relevant compliance matters to relevant U.S. government agencies, regulatory authorities, financial intelligence units, and law enforcement bodies, and fully cooperating with any and all inquiries, investigations, audits, examinations, or enforcement actions initiated by such authorities.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Comprehensive and Unequivocal Disclaimer of Liability and User Acknowledgment of Sole Responsibility:</strong> The TrekGuider Marketplace functions exclusively as a technology platform and intermediary venue to facilitate transactions and interactions between independent buyers and sellers of digital products and services and does not, and under no circumstances shall be construed to, provide legal advice, legal opinions, or legal guarantees of any kind or nature whatsoever regarding sanctions and export control compliance. Users bear sole, exclusive, absolute, and non-delegable responsibility for independently, proactively, and continuously verifying, assessing, and ensuring that their access to and use of the Marketplace, including any and all transactions, activities, and interactions conducted through the platform, fully, comprehensively, and perpetually complies with all applicable sanctions, export control laws, regulations, and directives. To the maximum extent legally permissible under applicable mandatory law:<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Comprehensive and Unqualified Disclaimer of Liability for Sanctions and Export Control Violations:</strong> TrekGuider Inc., its affiliates, subsidiaries, parent companies, successors, assigns, officers, directors, employees, consultants, agents, and representatives explicitly, unequivocally, and irrevocably disclaim any and all liability, responsibility, legal culpability, or financial exposure for any claims, demands, actions, causes of action, lawsuits, judgments, damages, losses, costs, penalties, fines, forfeitures, legal actions, regulatory enforcement proceedings, or other adverse consequences of any kind or nature whatsoever, whether foreseeable or unforeseeable, direct or indirect, actual or contingent, present or future, incurred by users, third parties, governmental authorities, regulatory agencies, or any other individuals or entities, arising from, relating to, or resulting from any violation, alleged violation, suspected violation, or perceived violation of sanctions, export control laws, or regulations by users of the Marketplace, or by any other party, whether such violation is intentional, unintentional, negligent, inadvertent, direct, indirect, or otherwise. This comprehensive and unqualified disclaimer of liability extends, without limitation, to any and all forms of legal, equitable, monetary, regulatory, or punitive remedies, sanctions, or consequences that may be imposed, assessed, or sought by any governmental authority, regulatory agency, or private party.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Unequivocal No Warranty of Compliance and User Assumption of All Risks:</strong> The TrekGuider Marketplace makes no representations, warranties, covenants, or guarantees, express or implied, statutory, contractual, or otherwise, that the Marketplace platform, its services, its functionalities, or any user activities conducted through, on, or in connection with the Marketplace will, can, or do ensure, guarantee, or otherwise warrant perpetual, uninterrupted, or error-free compliance with sanctions or export control laws, regulations, or directives. Users are solely, exclusively, and absolutely responsible for independently, proactively, and continuously verifying, assessing, and ensuring their own comprehensive, ongoing, and unimpeachable compliance with all applicable sanctions, export control laws, and regulations, and users explicitly acknowledge, understand, and agree that they are accessing and utilizing the TrekGuider Marketplace, and conducting any and all activities and transactions through the platform, entirely at their own volition, under their own exclusive control, and with their fully informed consent and express assumption of all associated legal, regulatory, financial, and reputational risks, liabilities, and consequences.<br>However, users acknowledge that these measures are discretionary and do not guarantee the complete and infallible prevention of all potential violations.<br><br></p><p><br></p>',
