hin the Refund Policy, as set forth in Section 6 of this Terms and Conditions and elsewhere in these Terms and Conditions. For absolute clarity, and without limiting the generality of the foregoing, you explicitly acknowledge and agree that in no event shall you be entitled to any remedies, recourse, or compensation beyond the express refund remedies set forth in the Refund Policy, and that TrekGuider Inc. shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, special, punitive, or exemplary damages, or any loss of profits, revenues, data, or use, arising from or related to any digital delivery issues, technical failures, or delays.</p><h3><strong>5.3. User Responsibility for Download and Access</strong></h3><p>Upon your valid and authorized purchase of digital products through the Marketplace, the Seller bears the sole and exclusive responsibility for diligently and effectively making the purchased digital product available for download or access by you, the Buyer, through the designated electronic delivery mechanisms facilitated by the Marketplace platform. Correspondingly, you, as the Buyer, bear the sole, exclusive, and non-delegable responsibility for proactively ensuring that you possess and maintain at all times the requisite compatible software, adequate hardware, stable internet connectivity, sufficient technical proficiency, and any and all other technical prerequisites that may be reasonably necessary or advisable to successfully download, access, utilize, and enjoy the purchased digital products. For absolute clarity, and without limiting the generality of the foregoing, you explicitly acknowledge, understand, and agree that the Marketplace, TrekGuider Inc., its affiliates, officers, directors, employees, agents, and representatives, shall bear no responsibility or liability whatsoever for any failure, inability, or impediment on your part to successfully access, download, utilize, or enjoy purchased digital products that arises, directly or indirectly, from or in connection with any limitations, deficiencies, or inadequacies in your own software, hardware, internet access, technical infrastructure, or technical skills.</p>',

      'paragraph-6' => '<h2><strong>6. Content Policy</strong></h2><h3><strong>6.1. User-Generated Content</strong></h3><p>Users, particularly sellers in the context of product listings, are exclusively and entirely responsible and liable for any and all content they affirmatively and voluntarily upload, post, transmit, distribute, or otherwise make available on or through the Marketplace platform, including, but not limited to, product descriptions, product images, promotional materials, reviews, comments, forum posts, articles, and any other forms of textual, visual, audio, or multimedia content (collectively, "User Content"). You, as a user, explicitly warrant, represent, and covenant that all User Content submitted, uploaded, published, or disseminated by you on the Marketplace will, at all times, fully comply with all applicable international, federal, state, and local laws, statutes, ordinances, regulations, and administrative rules, and will not infringe, misappropriate, or otherwise violate the intellectual property rights, proprietary rights, privacy rights, publicity rights, contractual rights, or any other rights of any third party, individual, or entity. It is your sole and non-delegable responsibility to ensure that you possess and maintain all necessary licenses, permissions, consents, and authorizations to lawfully utilize, reproduce, adapt, modify, display, distribute, and sublicense all elements of your User Content on the Marketplace platform.</p><h3><strong>6.2. Moderation and Enforcement</strong></h3><p>The Marketplace explicitly reserves, and shall at all times retain, the absolute, unfettered, discretionary, and non-reviewable right, but not the obligation, to actively monitor, screen, review, moderate, edit, modify, refuse to publish, remove, delete, disable access to, or relocate any and all User Content that, in the Marketplace\'s sole and exclusive judgment, is determined to be in violation of these Terms and Conditions, any applicable Marketplace policies, or any applicable law or regulation, or is otherwise deemed by the Marketplace, in its sole and unappealable discretion, to be inappropriate, unwelcome, objectionable, detrimental to the Marketplace, its users, or its community, or to pose an unacceptable risk of legal, regulatory, financial, reputational, or operational harm to the Marketplace. The Marketplace unequivocally reserves the right to exercise such moderation and enforcement rights and remedies at any time, without any prior notice, explanation, or opportunity for appeal to the affected user or seller. Content deemed inappropriate or violative may include, but is not limited to, content that is misleading, deceptive, inaccurate, outdated, of low quality, or that negatively impacts, or has the potential to negatively impact, the user experience on the Marketplace, even if such content does not explicitly or demonstrably violate any specific laws or regulations. The Marketplace shall possess sole, exclusive, and unreviewable discretion to determine, in any given instance, what User Content is deemed to be in violation of these Terms and Conditions or is otherwise deemed to be inappropriate, unwelcome, or objectionable, and any such determination shall be final, binding, and non-appealable. The Marketplace\'s discretionary moderation and enforcement actions may be undertaken through automated systems, manual review processes, or a combination thereof, at the Marketplace\'s sole option and discretion.</p>',

      'paragraph-7' => '<h2><strong>7. Policy on Counterfeit or Infringing Products</strong></h2><p>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Absolute, Unequivocal, and Zero-Tolerance Prohibition of Counterfeit and Intellectual Property Infringement:</strong> The TrekGuider Marketplace unequivocally maintains, rigorously enforces, and publicly affirms a strict, absolute, and zero-tolerance policy regarding the listing, offer for sale, sale, distribution, promotion, advertising, marketing, or other commercial exploitation of counterfeit products and any and all products that infringe, misappropriate, or otherwise violate the intellectual property rights, proprietary rights, or any other legal rights of others. This comprehensive, unwavering, and non-negotiable prohibition explicitly encompasses all forms of intellectual property, including, but not limited to, copyrights, trademarks, patents, trade secrets, design rights, rights of publicity, moral rights, and any and all other analogous proprietary rights recognized in any jurisdiction worldwide. The Marketplace is resolutely, proactively, and demonstrably committed to vigorously protecting intellectual property rights, fostering a marketplace environment characterized by authenticity, originality, and integrity, and aggressively deterring, detecting, preventing, and eradicating all forms of intellectual property infringement, counterfeiting, piracy, and related illicit activities.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Strict, Sole, and Non-Delegable User Responsibility and Liability for Product Authenticity, Legality, and Non-Infringement:</strong> Users, and particularly sellers offering products for sale on the Marketplace, bear sole, exclusive, absolute, unwavering, and non-delegable responsibility and liability for proactively, diligently, and continuously ensuring, verifying, and unequivocally demonstrating that any and all products they offer, sell, promote, distribute, or otherwise make available through the Marketplace are, and will at all times remain, unequivocally, demonstrably, and verifiably authentic, original, bona fide, and legally compliant works, and are wholly and demonstrably authorized for sale, distribution, and commercial exploitation in all relevant jurisdictions. Users are strictly, absolutely, and unconditionally prohibited from utilizing the Marketplace, directly or indirectly, overtly or covertly, to offer, sell, promote, distribute, or otherwise make available any products that are counterfeit, fraudulent, deceptive, knock-offs, imitations, replicas, unauthorized copies, or infringing goods, or any products that otherwise infringe, misappropriate, or violate, in any manner whatsoever, the intellectual property rights, proprietary rights, or other legal rights of any third parties, individuals, entities, or rights holders. This comprehensive, universal, and unqualified prohibition applies rigorously, uniformly, and without limitation to all categories of digital products listed, offered, or sold on the Marketplace, including, but not limited to, guides, maps, itineraries, travel guides, software, e-books, templates, multimedia content, and any other forms of digital content, services, or technologies.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Proactive, Discretionary, and Non-Exhaustive Marketplace Verification, Monitoring, and Enforcement Efforts:</strong> While the TrekGuider Marketplace is demonstrably dedicated to implementing robust, proactive, and continuously evolving measures to diligently detect, rigorously prevent, and swiftly remove the listing and sale of counterfeit and infringing products, users explicitly acknowledge, understand, and agree that these efforts are discretionary, non-exhaustive, and do not guarantee the complete and infallible identification and removal of all counterfeit or infringing products. Accordingly, users explicitly acknowledge, understand, and agree that the Marketplace may, at its sole, exclusive, unfettered, discretionary, and non-reviewable option, implement various verification, monitoring, and enforcement procedures, which may or may not be consistently or uniformly applied across all product listings or seller accounts, and which may include, but are not limited to, the illustrative, non-binding, and non-comprehensive examples enumerated below:<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Automated and Algorithmic Screening of Product Listings:</strong> Employing sophisticated, continuously enhanced, and dynamically adaptive automated screening systems, intelligent algorithms, machine learning tools, artificial intelligence-driven analytics, and proprietary detection methodologies to continuously scan, analyze, and flag product listings, descriptions, titles, images, metadata, and related content for keywords, textual patterns, visual indicators, branding elements, pricing anomalies, and other indicia, characteristics, or anomalies that may, in the Marketplace\'s sole and exclusive judgment, suggest, indicate, or raise a reasonable suspicion of potential counterfeit or infringing products, or listings that otherwise violate this Policy.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Risk-Based Manual Quality Reviews and Audits by Marketplace Personnel:</strong> Conducting targeted, risk-based, and non-systematic manual quality reviews and audits of a non-representative sample of selected seller accounts, product listings, and transaction histories, prioritizing reviews based on a variety of factors, including, but not limited to, seller history, account tenure, sales volume, product category, user reports, rights holder complaints, algorithmic risk scoring, geographic risk indicators, and other criteria deemed relevant by the Marketplace in its sole and exclusive judgment, to proactively assess, evaluate, and subjectively opine upon, in a purely discretionary and non-binding manner, the perceived quality, authenticity, legality, and overall compliance of selected listings with this Policy and other applicable Marketplace policies and guidelines.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Proactive Cooperation, Information Sharing, and Intelligence Gathering Initiatives with Rights Holders and Intellectual Property Enforcement Agencies:</strong> Engaging in proactive cooperation, intelligence sharing, and information exchange initiatives with rights holders, brand owners, intellectual property enforcement organizations, industry associations, governmental agencies, regulatory authorities, and law enforcement bodies to facilitate, enhance, and optimize the verification of the authenticity, legality, and authorized distribution status of products offered on the Marketplace, to proactively identify and preemptively prevent listings of counterfeit or infringing products, and to promptly, effectively, and decisively address, remediate, and eradicate any and all identified or suspected instances of infringement, counterfeiting, or other violations of this Policy.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>User Reporting Mechanisms and Community-Based Enforcement Initiatives:</strong> Providing readily accessible, user-friendly, and conspicuously located mechanisms, channels, and functionalities for users, buyers, sellers, rights holders, intellectual property owners, and other stakeholders to easily and efficiently report suspected listings of counterfeit or infringing products, or any other potential violations of this Policy, and implementing efficient, streamlined, and demonstrably responsive internal procedures, protocols, and workflows for promptly investigating, thoroughly assessing, and decisively acting upon such user-submitted reports, leveraging community-based vigilance, crowdsourced intelligence, and user feedback to continuously enhance overall marketplace integrity, authenticity, and trustworthiness.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Clear, Accessible, and User-Friendly Procedures for Reporting Counterfeit or Infringing Products:</strong> If any user, buyer, seller, rights holder, intellectual property owner, or other concerned party reasonably believes, or possesses credible evidence to suggest, that a product listed, offered for sale, or sold on the TrekGuider Marketplace is, or may be, counterfeit, constitutes intellectual property infringement, or otherwise violates this Policy, such party is strongly encouraged, affirmatively requested, and ethically obligated to immediately notify the Marketplace through the readily accessible and conspicuously published reporting procedures meticulously outlined and comprehensively detailed in the Copyright Policy, which is hereby fully incorporated by reference into these Terms and Conditions and this Policy. The Marketplace unequivocally assures all reporting parties that all credible, substantiated, and good-faith reports of infringement, counterfeiting, or other violations of this Policy will be treated with the utmost seriousness, accorded the highest priority, and subjected to prompt, thorough, impartial, and demonstrably good-faith review, investigation, and responsive action by designated compliance personnel and/or automated enforcement systems.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Decisive, Unilateral, and Non-Reviewable Marketplace Actions and Enforcement Remedies for Violations of Counterfeit and Infringement Policy:</strong> The TrekGuider Marketplace explicitly reserves, and shall at all times retain, the unfettered, discretionary, non-reviewable, and unilaterally exercisable right to undertake any and all actions, enforcement remedies, punitive measures, and legal recourse options against any user, seller, account holder, or other party who is determined, in the Marketplace’s sole, exclusive, and unappealable judgment, to be engaged in, facilitating, enabling, or materially contributing to the listing, offer for sale, sale, distribution, promotion, advertising, marketing, or other commercial exploitation of counterfeit or infringing products, or who is otherwise found to be in violation of this Policy. Such decisive, unilateral, and non-reviewable actions and enforcement remedies may include, without limitation, any one or more of the following:<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Immediate and Unilateral Listing Removal, Content Takedown, and Service Disruption:</strong> Summary, immediate, and unilateral removal, deletion, disabling of access to, permanent takedown, or comprehensive suppression of any and all product listings, offers for sale, promotional materials, advertising content, or other associated content that are reasonably suspected of being counterfeit, infringing, or otherwise in violation of this Policy, without any prior notice, explanation, or opportunity for appeal or remediation afforded to the affected user or seller. The Marketplace further reserves the right to temporarily or permanently disrupt, suspend, limit, or terminate any or all services, functionalities, or platform access available to sellers or users found to be in violation of this Policy.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Issuance of Formal Warnings, Censure Notices, and Mandatory Corrective Action Demands:</strong> Issuing formal written warnings, official notices of policy violation, and mandatory demands for immediate corrective action, remediation, and verifiable cessation of infringing conduct to sellers or users who are determined to be in violation of this Policy, requiring prompt, complete, and demonstrably effective remediation of all identified deficiencies, violations, and non-compliant practices, and implementation of robust, verifiable, and demonstrably effective preventative measures to avoid, deter, and preemptively mitigate future violations of this Policy.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Temporary or Permanent Account Suspension, Indefinite Account Termination, and Platform-Wide Ban:</strong> Imposing temporary suspension of account privileges, selling capabilities, transaction functionalities, or access to the Marketplace platform, or permanent and irrevocable termination of user accounts, seller accounts, and all associated privileges, access rights, benefits, and platform functionalities, coupled with a permanent, platform-wide, and universally applicable ban on any and all future access to or use of the TrekGuider Marketplace platform, for repeat, egregious, willful, malicious, or persistently repeated violations of this Policy, or for any single violation or series of related violations that are determined by the Marketplace, in its sole and exclusive judgment, to cause significant, irreparable, or systemic harm to the Marketplace, its users, rights holders, or the broader Marketplace community.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Permanent Withholding, Freezing, Impoundment, and Irrevocable Forfeiture of Seller Funds, Account Balances, and Pending Payouts:</strong> Temporarily or permanently withholding, freezing, impounding, or irrevocably forfeiting seller funds, account balances, pending payouts, accrued earnings, and any other monetary consideration otherwise due or owing to Seller, in whole or in part, pending thorough investigation, definitive resolution of all infringement claims, and to offset, recoup, and fully compensate the Marketplace, rights holders, buyers, and other injured parties for any and all damages, losses, costs, expenses, and harms, of any kind or nature whatsoever, incurred or continue demonstrably resulting from, or proximately caused by, Seller’s violations, or alleged violations, of this Policy on Counterfeit or Infringing Products, or any related Marketplace policies, terms, or guidelines.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Mandatory Chargebacks, Full Refunds, and Comprehensive Financial Recourse Obligations Imposed Upon Seller:</strong> Mandatory and non-negotiable imposition of chargebacks, full refunds, and comprehensive financial recourse obligations upon Seller for any and all purchases of counterfeit or infringing products by buyers through the Marketplace platform, with Seller bearing sole, exclusive, and absolute responsibility for fully, promptly, and unconditionally reimbursing, indemnifying, and holding harmless the Marketplace for the full and complete amount of all such chargebacks, refunds, transaction fees, penalties, fines, assessments, and associated administrative, operational, and legal costs, expenses, and harms, without any limitation whatsoever.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Proactive and Unrestricted Cooperation with Law Enforcement, Regulatory Authorities, and Rights Holders, Including Mandatory Disclosure of User Data and Transaction Records:</strong> Engaging in proactive, comprehensive, and unrestricted cooperation with law enforcement agencies, regulatory authorities, governmental bodies, intellectual property enforcement organizations, customs authorities, border protection agencies, and rights holders in connection with any and all investigations, enforcement actions, civil litigation, criminal prosecution, regulatory proceedings, and administrative actions pertaining to, arising from, or relating to the trafficking, distribution, offer for sale, or sale of counterfeit goods or intellectual property infringement through the Marketplace platform, including, without limitation, voluntary and mandatory disclosure, release, and provision of user data, account information, transaction records, communications logs, product listings, sales data, and any and all other relevant information, documentation, and evidence to facilitate law enforcement efforts, regulatory compliance initiatives, and rights holders’ enforcement actions, without any prior notice to or consent from Seller or any other user.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Comprehensive, Unequivocal, and Irrevocable Disclaimer of Liability and Mandatory User Acknowledgment of Risk, Due Diligence, and Indemnification Obligations:</strong> The TrekGuider Marketplace functions exclusively and solely as an online technology platform and intermediary venue to facilitate transactions and interactions between independent, unaffiliated, and autonomous buyers and sellers of digital products and services. The Marketplace does not, and under no circumstances shall be construed to, guarantee, warrant, represent, or covenant, either expressly or impliedly, directly or indirectly, the absolute authenticity, legality, originality, non-infringement, merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, safety, quality, or suitability of any products offered for sale, sold, purchased, or distributed by sellers or other users on the platform. To the maximum extent permitted by applicable mandatory law, and without limiting the generality of any other disclaimers, limitations of liability, or indemnification obligations set forth in these Terms and Conditions or elsewhere in any Marketplace policies:<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Comprehensive and Unqualified Disclaimer of Liability for Counterfeit or Infringing Products and Related Harms:</strong> TrekGuider Inc., its affiliates, subsidiaries, parent companies, successors, assigns, officers, directors, employees, agents, and representatives explicitly, unequivocally, and irrevocably disclaim any and all liability, responsibility, legal culpability, or financial exposure for any claims, demands, actions, causes of action, lawsuits, judgments, damages, losses, costs, expenses, or harms of any kind or nature whatsoever, whether foreseeable or unforeseeable, direct or indirect, actual or contingent, present or future, incurred by buyers, sellers, rights holders, intellectual property owners, regulatory authorities, governmental agencies, or any other third parties, individuals, or entities, arising from, relating to, or resulting from the listing, offer for sale, sale, purchase, use, distribution, promotion, advertising, marketing, or other commercial exploitation of counterfeit products or products that infringe, misappropriate, or violate intellectual property rights, proprietary rights, or other legal rights by sellers or users on the Marketplace platform. This comprehensive and unqualified disclaimer explicitly extends to, without limitation, any and all claims, demands, actions, causes of action, lawsuits, judgments, damages, losses, costs, expenses, or harms sounding in contract, tort, equity, statute, regulation, or otherwise, including, but not limited to, claims for direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, special, punitive, or exemplary damages, loss of profits, loss of revenue, loss of business opportunities, business interruption, reputational harm, emotional distress, mental anguish, pain and suffering, personal injury, property damage, economic loss, and any and all other forms of economic or non-economic loss, injury, or harm.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Mandatory User Assumption of All Risks, Affirmative Due Diligence Obligation, and Indemnification of Marketplace:</strong> All users, and particularly buyers contemplating or engaging in purchase transactions on the Marketplace, explicitly, knowingly, voluntarily, and irrevocably acknowledge, understand, and agree that they are accessing and utilizing the TrekGuider Marketplace and purchasing digital products offered by independent, unaffiliated, and autonomous sellers entirely at their own volition, personal risk, and informed consent. Buyers are hereby strongly, affirmatively, and unequivocally advised, cautioned, and legally obligated to exercise utmost vigilance, extreme caution, reasonable skepticism, and comprehensive, rigorous, and demonstrably effective due diligence, independent verification, and proactive risk assessment when evaluating product listings, assessing seller credentials, scrutinizing product descriptions, and making any and all purchasing decisions on the Marketplace platform. Buyers are solely, exclusively, and absolutely responsible and liable for conducting their own independent investigations, verifications, and assessments of product authenticity, legality, originality, non-infringement status, quality, suitability, and fitness for purpose prior to completing any purchase transaction, and for assuming and bearing any and all risks, hazards, and potential adverse consequences associated with or arising from any such purchase transactions. Furthermore, and without limiting the generality of the foregoing, all users, and particularly buyers, explicitly agree to fully, unconditionally, and irrevocably indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the Marketplace, TrekGuider Inc., its affiliates, officers, directors, employees, agents, and representatives from and against any and all claims, demands, actions, causes of action, lawsuits, judgments, damages, losses, costs, and expenses of any kind or nature whatsoever (including reasonable attorneys\' fees, expert witness fees, and court costs) arising from, relating to, or resulting from the purchase, use, or reliance upon any products purchased or obtained through the Marketplace platform, including, but not limited to, any claims or losses arising from or relating to allegations of counterfeit products or intellectual property infringement.</p>',

      'paragraph-8' => '<h2><strong>8. User Conduct and Community Guidelines</strong></h2><p>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Preamble: Fostering a Positive, Respectful, Safe, and Lawful Marketplace Community:</strong> The TrekGuider Marketplace is steadfastly dedicated to cultivating, promoting, and rigorously maintaining a consistently positive, demonstrably respectful, unequivocally safe, and strictly lawful online community environment for all users, encompassing buyers, sellers, content creators, visitors, and any and all other participants in the multifaceted Marketplace ecosystem. These comprehensive User Conduct and Community Guidelines ("Guidelines"), which are fully integrated into and constitute an inseparable, integral, and legally binding component of the overarching Terms and Conditions, meticulously delineate, comprehensively articulate, and unequivocally mandate the expected standards of conduct, ethical principles, behavioral norms, and legally enforceable obligations for all users of the Marketplace platform. By accessing, utilizing, or participating in any aspect of the TrekGuider Marketplace, each user explicitly, knowingly, voluntarily, and irrevocably acknowledges, understands, and affirmatively agrees to be perpetually bound by, and to consistently, diligently, and scrupulously adhere to, these Guidelines, in addition to all other provisions, terms, conditions, covenants, obligations, and disclaimers meticulously set forth within the complete and legally controlling Terms and Conditions agreement.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Mandatory and Non-Derogable Standards of Expected User Conduct, Ethical Principles, and Behavioral Norms:</strong> All users of the TrekGuider Marketplace are unconditionally, unequivocally, and non-derogably required, legally obligated, and ethically bound to conduct themselves, and to interact with one another, with Marketplace personnel, and with the platform itself, with unwavering respect, unfailing courtesy, scrupulous ethical probity, and demonstrably professional decorum, at all times, in all contexts, and throughout the entire duration of their engagement with the Marketplace. Prohibited conduct, which is strictly, absolutely, and unequivocally forbidden and will be subject to immediate, decisive, and non-reviewable enforcement action by the Marketplace, includes, but is not limited to, the following illustrative, non-exhaustive, and non-mutually exclusive categories of unacceptable, prohibited, and sanctionable behavior:<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Imperative of Respectful, Civil, and Constructive Communication in All Interactions:</strong> Users are unconditionally, unequivocally, and non-derogably obligated to engage in consistently constructive, demonstrably civil, and unequivocally respectful communication in any and all interactions, exchanges, correspondences, and communications conducted on, through, or in connection with the Marketplace platform, irrespective of the medium, modality, or context of such interactions. The use of offensive language, personal attacks, ad hominem arguments, insults, pejorative epithets, derogatory remarks, inflammatory rhetoric, inflammatory statements, or any other forms of uncivil, discourteous, disrespectful, unprofessional, or otherwise inappropriate communication is strictly, absolutely, and unequivocally prohibited and will not be tolerated under any circumstances, and will be subject to immediate and decisive enforcement action by the Marketplace.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Absolute, Unequivocal, and Zero-Tolerance Prohibition of Harassment, Bullying, Discrimination, Hate Speech, and Promotion of Violence or Hatred:</strong> Users are unequivocally, absolutely, and without exception prohibited from engaging in any form of harassment, bullying, cyberstalking, intimidation, menacing behavior, or threatening conduct, whether direct or indirect, overt or covert, express or implied, directed towards other users, Marketplace personnel, rights holders, or any other individuals or entities associated with the platform or the broader Marketplace community. Discrimination, prejudice, bias, disparagement, or denigration based on race, ethnicity, national origin, religion, creed, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, marital status, parental status, familial status, disability, medical condition, genetic information, age, socioeconomic status, veteran status, political affiliation, or any other legally protected characteristic, status, or attribute is strictly, comprehensively, and unequivocally prohibited and will be subject to immediate, decisive, and non-reviewable enforcement action by the Marketplace. The Marketplace further maintains, rigorously enforces, and publicly affirms a strict, absolute, and zero-tolerance policy regarding hate speech, incitement to violence, promotion of hatred, or any other forms of expression, communication, or conduct that denigrate, dehumanize, demonize, stereotype, marginalize, incite violence against, promote hatred towards, or otherwise foster animosity, hostility, contempt, or discriminatory animus towards individuals or groups based on their protected characteristics, statuses, or attributes, as enumerated herein or as otherwise defined and protected by applicable law.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Unconditional and Non-Derogable Requirement for Honesty, Transparency, Probity, and Unwavering Integrity in All Marketplace Activities:</strong> Users are affirmatively, unconditionally, and non-derogably obligated to conduct any and all interactions, transactions, activities, and communications on the Marketplace with the utmost honesty, transparency, probity, ethical rectitude, and unwavering integrity, and in full and scrupulous compliance with all applicable ethical standards, industry best practices, and principles of fair dealing. Engaging in deceptive practices, misrepresentation, fraudulent schemes, manipulative tactics, bad-faith negotiation, unfair dealing, dissemination of misinformation, propagation of disinformation, concealment of material facts, or any other forms of dishonest, unethical, misleading, or commercially unreasonable conduct is strictly, absolutely, and unequivocally prohibited and will be subject to severe sanctions, decisive enforcement remedies, and potential legal referral, without limitation.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Unconditional and Non-Derogable Compliance Mandate with All Applicable Laws, Regulations, and Marketplace Policies:</strong> All user conduct, activities, transactions, and content publication on the Marketplace platform must, at all times, fully, scrupulously, and unconditionally comply with all applicable international, federal, state, and local laws, statutes, ordinances, regulations, administrative rules, and legally binding directives, as well as with all Marketplace policies, guidelines, rules, and procedures, including, without limitation, these Terms and Conditions, the Content Policy, the Copyright Policy, the Privacy Policy, the Payment Policy, the Seller Agreement, the Dispute Resolution Policy, the Cookie Policy, the Data Processing Agreement, the Advertising Policy, and all other policies, guidelines, rules, and agreements incorporated by reference therein or otherwise promulgated by the Marketplace from time to time. Users bear sole, exclusive, absolute, and non-delegable responsibility for ensuring their comprehensive, perpetual, and ongoing compliance with all such legal and policy requirements, and shall be solely liable and responsible for any and all consequences arising from any actual or alleged violation or non-compliance.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Specific, Mandatory, and Non-Derogable Rules Governing Interactions Between Buyers and Sellers and Utilization of Marketplace Communication Features:</strong> The TrekGuider Marketplace provides designated platform features, functionalities, and communication channels to facilitate direct, transparent, and efficient interaction between buyers and sellers, primarily through publicly accessible product reviews, seller feedback mechanisms, and community comment sections. Users are unconditionally, unequivocally, and non-derogably expected and legally obligated to meticulously, scrupulously, and perpetually adhere to the following specific guidelines, mandatory rules, and legally enforceable obligations of engagement when utilizing these interactive features and communication channels:<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Imperative of Constructive, Demonstrably Relevant, and Verifiably Experience-Based Reviews, Comments, and Feedback:</strong> Product reviews, seller feedback, and community comments posted, submitted, or otherwise disseminated by users on the Marketplace platform must be consistently constructive, demonstrably relevant to the specific digital product, service, seller, or Marketplace feature or functionality being evaluated or discussed, and genuinely, verifiably, and demonstrably based upon the user’s direct, personal, and authentic experience with the product, service, seller, or feature in question. The posting, submission, or dissemination of irrelevant, off-topic, gratuitously negative, unsubstantiated, спекулятивные, or spam-like comments, reviews, or feedback is strictly, absolutely, and unequivocally prohibited and will be subject to immediate moderation, content removal, and/or other enforcement actions by the Marketplace, in its sole and non-reviewable discretion.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Unconditional and Non-Derogable Imperative of Honest, Impartial, Objective, and Demonstrably Fair Feedback, Assessments, and Evaluations:</strong> Users are affirmatively, unconditionally, and non-derogably obligated to provide honest, demonstrably impartial, objectively fair, and verifiably accurate feedback, assessments, and evaluations in any and all reviews, comments, and feedback posted, submitted, or otherwise disseminated on the Marketplace platform. The posting, submission, or dissemination of fake, fraudulent, deceptive, or materially misleading reviews, comments, or feedback, or any attempts to engage in review manipulation, incentivized reviews, compensated reviews, or review extortion, are strictly, absolutely, and unequivocally prohibited and will be subject to severe enforcement action, including, without limitation, permanent account termination, forfeiture of funds, and potential legal referral for civil or criminal prosecution, as warranted.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Unconditional and Non-Derogable Maintenance of Professional, Courteous, Civil, and Respectful Communication Tone in All Interactions:</strong> Users are unconditionally, unequivocally, and non-derogably required to maintain a consistently professional, demonstrably courteous, unequivocally civil, and unfailingly respectful tone, demeanor, and communicative style in any and all communications, interactions, reviews, comments, and feedback posted, submitted, or otherwise disseminated on the Marketplace platform. The use of personal attacks, ad hominem arguments, unprofessional language, profanity, obscenities, vulgarities, sexually suggestive language, or any other forms of discourteous, uncivil, disrespectful, unprofessional, or otherwise inappropriate communication is strictly, absolutely, and unequivocally prohibited and will be subject to immediate moderation, content removal, account suspension, and/or other enforcement actions by the Marketplace, in its sole and non-reviewable discretion.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Absolute Prohibition of Private Messaging Functionality and Mandatory Utilization of Public Communication Channels for Marketplace-Related Interactions:</strong> The TrekGuider Marketplace, in its sole and exclusive operational discretion, does not currently offer, and explicitly, absolutely, and unequivocally prohibits the use of, any private messaging, direct messaging, encrypted messaging, ephemeral messaging, or non-public communication channels, features, or functionalities between users of the platform for purposes of conducting Marketplace-related communications, transactions, or interactions. All communication, correspondence, and interactions between buyers and sellers, and between users generally, that pertain to, arise from, or relate to the Marketplace platform, its services, or any transactions conducted thereon, must be exclusively, transparently, and verifiably conducted through publicly visible, readily accessible, comprehensively auditable, and permanently archived communication channels, features, and functionalities expressly and deliberately provided by the Marketplace platform for such purposes, such as, by way of example and without limitation, product reviews, seller feedback sections, community comment sections, and publicly accessible user forums, to ensure maximum transparency, accountability, community oversight, dispute traceability, and regulatory compliance. Any attempts by users to circumvent, bypass, or otherwise subvert this mandatory requirement for public communication by utilizing private messaging channels, encrypted communications, or off-platform communication methods for Marketplace-related interactions are strictly, absolutely, and unequivocally prohibited and will be subject to immediate and decisive enforcement action by the Marketplace, in its sole and non-reviewable discretion.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Detailed, Mandatory, and Non-Derogable Content Publication Guidelines and Elevated Quality Standards for All User-Generated and Seller-Provided Content:</strong> In addition to the comprehensive categories of prohibited content meticulously delineated and explicitly proscribed within the overarching Content Policy, users are further expected, unconditionally required, and legally obligated to rigorously, scrupulously, and perpetually adhere to the following detailed guidelines, elevated quality standards, and legally enforceable mandates when publishing, uploading, transmitting, or otherwise making available any and all forms of content on the TrekGuider Marketplace platform, including, without limitation, product listings, product descriptions, seller profiles, user profiles, comments, reviews, forum posts, articles, blog entries, and any other user-generated or seller-provided content, irrespective of its format, medium, or intended audience:<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Unconditional Imperative of High Content Quality, Demonstrable Factual Accuracy, Contextual Relevance, Substantive Value, and Tangible User Benefit:</strong> Users are affirmatively, unconditionally, and non-derogably required to consistently, diligently, and perpetually strive to publish, upload, transmit, and otherwise make available only demonstrably high-quality, verifiably factually accurate, contextually relevant, substantively valuable, demonstrably beneficial, and unequivocally lawful content that enriches the Marketplace community, enhances user experience, fosters informed decision-making, and contributes positively and constructively to the overall quality, utility, trustworthiness, and legal integrity of the platform. All published content must be meticulously well-written, grammatically correct, stylistically coherent, logically organized, comprehensively informative, demonstrably free of material errors, significant omissions, factual inaccuracies, or misleading statements, and presented in a clear, concise, and readily comprehensible manner that is optimally accessible and beneficial to the intended audience of users.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Strict and Non-Derogable Requirement for Content Relevance and Appropriateness to Explicitly Defined Marketplace Focus and Thematic Scope:</strong> Users are unconditionally, unequivocally, and non-derogably obligated to ensure that any and all content published, uploaded, transmitted, or otherwise made available on the Marketplace platform is demonstrably, directly, and unambiguously relevant to the Marketplace’s explicitly defined and narrowly circumscribed focus on digital tourist products, travel-related content, and the specific needs, interests, and informational requirements of the platform’s user base, which is primarily, predominantly, and intentionally comprised of individual travelers, tourists, travel enthusiasts, and individuals and entities seeking digital resources, tools, and information to facilitate travel planning, navigation, experiential enhancement, and tourism-related commercial activities. The posting, publication, uploading, transmission, or dissemination of content that is patently off-topic, demonstrably irrelevant to the Marketplace’s core subject matter, or otherwise inappropriate, unsuitable, incongruous, or demonstrably inconsistent with or tangential to the Marketplace’s explicitly defined intended audience, core purpose, or narrowly circumscribed thematic focus is strictly, absolutely, and unequivocally prohibited and will be subject to immediate moderation, content removal, account suspension, and/or other enforcement actions by the Marketplace, in its sole and non-reviewable discretion.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Mandatory and Non-Derogable Requirements for Content Originality, Proper Attribution, and Comprehensive Copyright Compliance:</strong> Users are unequivocally, unconditionally, and non-derogably required to ensure that any and all content they publish, upload, transmit, or otherwise make available on the Marketplace platform is demonstrably original to the publishing user, or, in instances where third-party content, copyrighted materials, or proprietary intellectual property are incorporated, integrated, or utilized, that the publishing user has diligently, proactively, and verifiably obtained, and can readily demonstrate, upon first demand by the Marketplace or any rights holder, all necessary, valid, and legally enforceable rights, licenses, permissions, consents, waivers, and authorizations to lawfully and legitimately utilize, reproduce, adapt, modify, translate, create derivative works of, distribute, publicly display, publicly perform, digitally transmit, and sublicense such third-party content, copyrighted materials, or proprietary intellectual property on the Marketplace platform, in all relevant media, formats, and jurisdictions, for the full intended duration of such utilization. Users are further unconditionally, unequivocally, and non-derogably obligated to meticulously, conspicuously, and comprehensively provide proper attribution, credit, and acknowledgment to all original rights holders, authors, creators, and sources of any and all third-party content, copyrighted materials, or proprietary intellectual property utilized in their publications, strictly adhering to all applicable copyright laws, intellectual property regulations, licensing terms, attribution conventions, and industry best practices for proper citation and scholarly attribution.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Comprehensive, Absolute, and Zero-Tolerance Prohibition of Spam, Unsolicited Advertising, and Excessive or Egregious Self-Promotion:</strong> Users are strictly, absolutely, and unequivocally prohibited from utilizing the TrekGuider Marketplace platform, or any of its features, functionalities, or communication channels, for the posting, transmission, dissemination, propagation, or other making available of spam, unsolicited commercial advertising, unauthorized marketing solicitations, deceptive promotional materials, or any other forms of unsolicited, unwelcome, intrusive, irrelevant, or commercially inappropriate communications, solicitations, or content that detract from the user experience, disrupt the platform’s intended functionality, undermine the integrity of the Marketplace community, or otherwise violate the explicitly stated spirit, manifest intent, and express provisions of these Community Guidelines and the overarching Terms and Conditions. While limited, contextually relevant, demonstrably value-added, and non-intrusive self-promotional content may be conditionally permissible in certain specifically designated areas of the Marketplace platform, and solely to the limited extent explicitly, affirmatively, and unambiguously authorized by the Marketplace in its sole and exclusive discretion on a case-by-case basis, the posting, uploading, transmission, or other dissemination of excessive, repetitive, indiscriminate, or overtly promotional self-promotional content, or any self-promotional content that is reasonably deemed by the Marketplace, in its sole and unreviewable judgment, to be disruptive, unwelcome, inappropriate, commercially intrusive, or detrimental to the user experience, the Marketplace community, or the platform’s overall integrity, is strictly, absolutely, and unequivocally prohibited and will be subject to immediate moderation, content removal, account suspension, and/or other enforcement actions by the Marketplace, in its sole and non-reviewable discretion.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Decisive, Unilateral, and Non-Reviewable Enforcement Actions and Consequential Remedies for Any and All Violations of Community Guidelines:</strong> Any and all violations of these User Conduct and Community Guidelines, as definitively determined by the TrekGuider Marketplace in its sole and exclusive judgment and non-reviewable discretion, may, and shall, without limitation, result in the immediate, automatic, and non-appealable imposition, implementation, and rigorous enforcement of any one or more of the following enforcement actions, punitive sanctions, and remedial measures, without any prior notice, explanation, opportunity for remediation, or right of appeal whatsoever afforded to the violating user, seller, or account holder.<strong><em> </em></strong>This list of enforcement actions is illustrative and non-exhaustive, and the Marketplace reserves the right to implement any other enforcement actions, punitive sanctions, and remedial measures deemed necessary or advisable in its sole and exclusive discretion:<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Issuance of Formal Warnings, Official Censure Notices, and Mandatory Demands for Immediate Rectification:</strong> Issuance of formal written warnings, official notices of policy violation, and public or private censures to users definitively determined to be in violation of these Guidelines, meticulously documenting the specific nature, scope, and severity of the violation, demanding immediate, verifiable, and permanent cessation of the prohibited conduct, and explicitly threatening further, more severe, and potentially irreversible enforcement action for any and all continued or repeated non-compliance.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Summary, Unilateral, and Non-Reviewable Content Moderation, Editing, and Removal Actions:</strong> Immediate, unilateral, and non-reviewable moderation, editing, modification, or complete and permanent removal, deletion, disabling of access to, and irreversible takedown of any and all content, communications, reviews, comments, forum posts, or other user-generated materials, irrespective of format or medium, that are definitively determined by the Marketplace, in its sole and exclusive judgment, to be in violation of these Guidelines, or otherwise deemed by the Marketplace, in its sole and unreviewable discretion, to be inappropriate, unwelcome, disruptive, offensive, harmful, or detrimental to the Marketplace community, the user experience, or the platform’s overall integrity, without any prior notice, explanation, or opportunity for appeal or remediation afforded to the affected user.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Temporary Suspension of Account Privileges, Functional Access, and Marketplace Features:</strong> Temporary suspension, limitation, restriction, or revocation of user account access, selling privileges, transaction functionalities, posting capabilities, communication functionalities, or any other features, functionalities, services, or privileges of the Marketplace platform, for a duration, scope, and severity determined by the Marketplace in its sole and exclusive discretion, for any and all repeated, persistent, egregious, willful, or demonstrably harmful violations of these Guidelines, or for any failure, refusal, or demonstrable unwillingness to promptly, completely, and verifiably remediate identified violations upon formal notification and mandatory demand for corrective action.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Permanent Account Termination, Irrevocable Platform Ban, and Forfeiture of Account Balances:</strong> Permanent and irrevocable termination of user accounts, seller accounts, and all associated privileges, access rights, benefits, and platform functionalities, coupled with a permanent, platform-wide, and universally applicable ban on any and all future access to or use of the TrekGuider Marketplace platform, for egregious, willful, malicious, intentional, or persistently repeated violations of these Guidelines, or for any violations that are definitively determined by the Marketplace, in its sole and exclusive judgment, to cause significant, irreparable, or systemic harm to the Marketplace, its users, its community, rights holders, or any other stakeholder in the Marketplace ecosystem. In conjunction with permanent account termination and platform ban, the Marketplace further reserves the absolute, non-reviewable, and unilaterally exercisable right to permanently withhold, freeze, impound, and irrevocably forfeit any and all seller funds, account balances, pending payouts, accrued earnings, and any other monetary consideration otherwise due or owing to the violating user or seller, in whole or in part, pending comprehensive investigation, definitive resolution of all outstanding issues, and to offset, recoup, and fully compensate the Marketplace, rights holders, buyers, and other injured parties for any and all damages, losses, costs, expenses, and harms incurred as a direct or indirect result of the user’s violations of these Community Guidelines.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Discretionary Implementation of Any and All Other Enforcement Actions, Punitive Sanctions, and Remedial Measures Deemed Necessary or Advisable:</strong> The TrekGuider Marketplace explicitly reserves, and shall at all times retain, the unfettered, discretionary, non-reviewable, and unilaterally exercisable right to implement any and all other enforcement actions, punitive sanctions, remedial measures, disciplinary actions, legal recourse options, or equitable remedies deemed necessary, appropriate, or advisable, in its sole and exclusive judgment, to comprehensively, effectively, and decisively address any and all actual or suspected violations of these Guidelines, to proactively deter future misconduct, to rigorously maintain the integrity, safety, civility, and ethical probity of the Marketplace community, and to comprehensively protect the rights, interests, and overall well-being of the Marketplace, its users, rights holders, and all other stakeholders in the broader Marketplace ecosystem.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Mandatory User Encouragement and Affirmative Ethical and Legal Obligation to Proactively Report Suspected Violations of Community Guidelines:</strong> To foster a robust, self-regulating, and community-driven environment of ethical conduct, mutual respect, and unwavering adherence to these Community Guidelines, all users of the TrekGuider Marketplace are strongly encouraged, affirmatively requested, ethically obligated, and legally bound to proactively, diligently, and continuously monitor the platform for any and all potential or suspected violations of these Community Guidelines and to promptly, effectively, and responsibly report any and all suspected violations, instances of misconduct, or inappropriate user behavior that they may encounter, witness, or become aware of on the Marketplace platform. Reports of violations should be submitted expeditiously through the designated contact channels outlined in Section 19 (Contact Information) of these Terms and Conditions, ensuring efficient, confidential, and demonstrably effective communication of user concerns, reports, and evidentiary submissions to designated Marketplace personnel and/or automated enforcement systems. The Marketplace unequivocally assures all reporting users that all credible, substantiated, and good-faith reports of violations will be treated with the utmost seriousness, accorded the highest priority, and subjected to prompt, thorough, and impartial review, investigation, and responsive action by designated compliance personnel and/or automated enforcement systems, with due consideration for user privacy, confidentiality, and protection against retaliatory actions.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Comprehensive and Unequivocal Disclaimer of Liability for User Conduct and Content and Reservation of Unfettered Marketplace Discretion:</strong> The TrekGuider Marketplace explicitly reserves, and shall at all times retain, the sole, exclusive, unfettered, discretionary, and non-reviewable right to interpret, construe, apply, enforce, and comprehensively modify these Community Guidelines, in their entirety or in any particular provision, at its sole, absolute, and unappealable discretion, without any prior notice, explanation, or opportunity for user input, comment, or objection. While these Guidelines are meticulously crafted and earnestly intended to proactively promote a demonstrably positive, consistently respectful, unequivocally safe, and strictly lawful community environment for all users of the TrekGuider Marketplace, the Marketplace, TrekGuider Inc., its affiliates, officers, directors, employees, agents, and representatives provide no representations, warranties, guarantees, or covenants, either express or implied, statutory, contractual, or otherwise, that all users will, at all times, uniformly, consistently, and infallibly adhere to each and every provision, principle, and expectation articulated within these Guidelines, or that the Marketplace will be capable of preventing, detecting, or effectively remediating all potential or actual violations of these Guidelines in every instance. To the maximum extent permitted by applicable mandatory law, and without limiting the generality of any other disclaimers, limitations of liability, or indemnification obligations set forth in these Terms and Conditions or elsewhere in any Marketplace policies:<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Comprehensive and Unqualified Disclaimer of Liability for User Conduct, User-Generated Content, and Inter-User Interactions:</strong> TrekGuider Inc., its affiliates, officers, directors, employees, agents, and representatives explicitly, unequivocally, and irrevocably disclaim any and all liability, responsibility, legal culpability, or financial exposure for any claims, demands, actions, causes of action, lawsuits, judgments, damages, losses, costs, expenses, or harms of any kind or nature whatsoever, whether foreseeable or unforeseeable, direct or indirect, actual or contingent, present or future, incurred by users, third parties, rights holders, or any other individuals or entities, arising from, relating to, or resulting from the conduct, behavior, communications, interactions, or user-generated content of any user of the TrekGuider Marketplace platform, including, without limitation, any conduct, behavior, communications, or content that may be reasonably or demonstrably deemed to be violative of these Community Guidelines, offensive, unwelcome, inappropriate, harmful, unethical, unlawful, or otherwise objectionable. This comprehensive and unqualified disclaimer explicitly extends to, without limitation, any and all claims, demands, actions, causes of action, lawsuits, judgments, damages, losses, costs, expenses, or harms sounding in contract, tort, equity, statute, regulation, or otherwise, including, but not limited to, claims for direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, special, punitive, or exemplary damages, emotional distress, reputational harm, economic loss, and any other form of harm or injury, whether foreseeable or unforeseeable, arising from user conduct or content on the Marketplace platform.<br>o&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Unequivocal No Guarantee of Perfect Community Adherence to Guidelines and User Assumption of All Inherent Platform Risks:</strong> The TrekGuider Marketplace explicitly does not, and under no circumstances shall be construed to, guarantee, warrant, represent, or covenant, either expressly or impliedly, directly or indirectly, that all users of the Marketplace platform will, at all times, perfectly, uniformly, consistently, and without exception, fully and completely adhere to each and every provision, principle, and expectation articulated within these Community Guidelines. The Marketplace acknowledges, and users explicitly understand, knowingly agree, and irrevocably accept, that, despite the Marketplace’s best faith efforts, diligent endeavors, and proactive measures to foster a positive, respectful, safe, and lawful community environment, the inherent nature of online platforms, user-generated content ecosystems, and interconnected digital environments inevitably entails a residual, non-negligible, and unavoidable risk of potential exposure to unwelcome, inappropriate, offensive, harmful, unethical, unlawful, or otherwise objectionable conduct or content, and that users are solely, exclusively, and absolutely responsible for exercising their own informed judgment, prudent discretion, reasonable vigilance, and comprehensive personal risk assessment when interacting with other users, consuming content, and engaging in any and all activities on the Marketplace platform.</p>',

      'paragraph-9' => '<h2><strong>9. Advertising Policy</strong></h2><h3><strong>9.1. Advertising on the Marketplace</strong></h3><p>The Marketplace explicitly reserves the right, exercisable in its sole and absolute discretion, to display advertisements, promotional content, sponsored listings, and other forms of commercial solicitations throughout various sections, pages, and functionalities of the platform, including, but not limited to, prominent placement within news and articles sections, blog entries, community forums, product listings, seller profiles, and user dashboards. Such advertisements may include, but are not limited to, contextual advertisements served through third-party advertising networks and programmatic advertising platforms, such as Google AdSense, as well as direct advertising placements, sponsored content integrations, affiliate marketing links, and promotional partnerships arranged and managed directly by the Marketplace. The types, formats, placement, frequency, and overall presentation of advertisements on the Marketplace are subject to change, modification, or removal at any time, without prior notice or explanation, in the Marketplace\'s sole and exclusive discretion. Advertisers, content creators participating in revenue-sharing programs, and all other parties providing advertising content for display on the Marketplace must, at all times, fully and scrupulously adhere to all applicable advertising guidelines, content policies, community standards, legal requirements, and ethical principles, as promulgated and enforced by the Marketplace from time to time.</p><h3><strong>9.2. Revenue Sharing with Content Authors (Advertising Revenue)</strong></h3><p>&nbsp;The Marketplace, at its sole discretion and as a purely voluntary and gratuitous incentive program, may offer a revenue-sharing program to selectively compensate content authors who contribute original, high-quality, and demonstrably valuable news articles, blog posts, editorial content, and other forms of informational or educational materials to the platform, as determined by the Marketplace in its sole and exclusive editorial judgment. This discretionary program, if and when offered, may allow eligible authors, as determined by the Marketplace, to potentially earn a purely discretionary and non-guaranteed portion of the net advertising revenue, if any, actually and demonstrably generated by the Marketplace directly and exclusively from advertisements specifically and directly displayed within, directly alongside, or immediately adjacent to their original articles, blog posts, or other qualifying content contributions, specifically limited to advertisements served through Google AdSense or similar third-party advertising networks programmatically integrated into the Marketplace platform.<br>&nbsp;The percentage of advertising revenue, if any, shared with eligible content authors, if and when such revenue sharing is offered by the Marketplace, is determined arbitrarily and unilaterally by the Marketplace, in its sole and exclusive discretion, and may be subject to change, modification, or complete termination at any time, with or without prior notice or explanation, and without any obligation, liability, or recourse of any kind or nature whatsoever on the part of the Marketplace. For illustrative and informational purposes only, and without creating any contractual obligation, legal commitment, or user entitlement, the Marketplace may, from time to time, elect, in its sole and unreviewable discretion, to utilize a tiered commission structure, which, if implemented, may hypothetically resemble the following non-binding, purely discretionary, and unilaterally modifiable commission levels:</p><p>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Level 1 Authors:</strong> May, at the Marketplace\'s sole discretion, hypothetically receive up to 40% of the advertising revenue, if any, demonstrably and directly generated from advertisements displayed in direct and immediate proximity to their qualifying articles, blog posts, or other content contributions, as definitively determined and meticulously calculated by the Marketplace through its internal, proprietary, and non-transparent revenue attribution methodologies and accounting practices.</p><p>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Level 2 Authors:</strong> May, at the Marketplace\'s sole discretion, hypothetically receive up to 30% of the advertising revenue, if any, demonstrably and directly generated from advertisements displayed in direct and immediate proximity to their qualifying articles, blog posts, or other content contributions, as definitively determined and meticulously calculated by the Marketplace through its internal, proprietary, and non-transparent revenue attribution methodologies and accounting practices.</p><p>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Level 3 Authors: </strong>May, at the Marketplace\'s sole discretion, hypothetically receive up to 20% of the advertising revenue, if any, demonstrably and directly generated from advertisements displayed in direct and immediate proximity to their qualifying articles, blog posts, or other content contributions, as definitively determined and meticulously calculated by the Marketplace through its internal, proprietary, and non-transparent revenue attribution methodologies and accounting practices.</p><p>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Level 4 Authors: </strong>May, at the Marketplace\'s sole discretion, hypothetically receive up to 10% of the advertising revenue, if any, demonstrably and directly generated from advertisements displayed in direct and immediate proximity to their qualifying articles, blog posts, or other content contributions, as definitively determined and meticulously calculated by the Marketplace through its internal, proprietary, and non-transparent revenue attribution methodologies and accounting practices.<br>&nbsp;These hypothetical, non-binding, and purely illustrative commission levels, if and when offered, may be arbitrarily based, in whole or in part, on the author\'s overall contribution, perceived content quality, demonstrable user engagement metrics, subjective editorial assessments, or any other criteria, factors, or considerations unilaterally determined and arbitrarily modified by the Marketplace from time to time, in its sole and unreviewable discretion, without any obligation to provide prior notice, justification, or transparency to content authors or other users. The Marketplace explicitly reserves the absolute, unfettered, and non-reviewable right to comprehensively modify, unilaterally alter, arbitrarily adjust, substantially curtail, or completely terminate the author level criteria, revenue sharing percentages, program eligibility requirements, payout schedules, or any and all other aspects of this purely discretionary and gratuitous advertising revenue sharing program at any time, with or without prior notice, explanation, or justification, and without incurring any liability or obligation of any kind or nature whatsoever to content authors, users, or any other party.<br>&nbsp;Revenue sharing payouts, if and when actually and voluntarily offered by the Marketplace, will be calculated and credited to eligible author accounts on a purely discretionary and non-guaranteed monthly basis, typically within an estimated and non-binding timeframe of 10–15 business days after the end of each calendar month, strictly subject to successful and error-free processing by third-party payment processors, such as Stripe, and further contingent upon numerous factors that are wholly outside the Marketplace\'s control, including, but not limited to, actual advertising revenue generation, advertiser payment defaults, fluctuations in advertising demand, changes in advertising network policies, and technical malfunctions or errors in revenue tracking and attribution systems. Authors must accrue and maintain a minimum verified and non-disputed balance of fifty United States dollars ($50.00 USD) in demonstrably attributable advertising revenue share earnings, as definitively determined and meticulously calculated by the Marketplace through its internal, proprietary, and non-transparent revenue attribution methodologies and accounting practices, before a withdrawal request can be even considered for potential discretionary processing by the Marketplace, consistent with the minimum withdrawal balance requirements applicable to sellers of digital products, as set forth in the Payment Policy and Seller Agreement. Any and all payouts, if and when actually and voluntarily offered and processed by the Marketplace, are explicitly and unconditionally subject to deduction of any and all applicable third-party payment processor transaction fees, currency conversion fees, withdrawal fees, and any other fees, charges, assessments, or deductions that may be imposed, assessed, or levied by third-party payment processors, intermediary financial institutions, or governmental authorities, as well as the comprehensive and controlling terms, conditions, limitations, restrictions, and disclaimers meticulously set forth in the Payment Policy, Seller Agreement, and these Terms and Conditions.<br>&nbsp;The Marketplace explicitly reserves the absolute, unfettered, discretionary, and non-reviewable right to comprehensively modify, unilaterally alter, arbitrarily adjust, substantially curtail, completely suspend, or permanently terminate this advertising revenue-sharing program, in whole or in part, at any time, for any reason, or for no reason whatsoever, with or without prior notice, explanation, or justification, and without incurring any liability or obligation of any kind or nature whatsoever to content authors, users, or any other party. The Marketplace provides no representations, warranties, covenants, or guarantees, either express or implied, statutory, contractual, or otherwise, that content authors will actually receive any specific level of advertising revenue, or any advertising revenue whatsoever, from their content contributions, as advertising revenue generation is inherently contingent upon numerous volatile, unpredictable, and uncontrollable factors that are wholly outside the Marketplace\'s control, including, but not limited to, overall website traffic, user engagement metrics, advertisement placement optimization, click-through rates, conversion rates, advertiser demand, seasonal fluctuations in advertising spending, macroeconomic conditions, changes in advertising network algorithms, and numerous other market-driven and technological variables that are subject to constant change and unpredictable volatility.</p><h3><strong>9.3. Disclaimer of Endorsement</strong></h3><p>You explicitly acknowledge, understand, and agree that the marketplace, TrekGuider inc., its affiliates, officers, directors, employees, agents, and representatives, do not, under any circumstances, endorse, sponsor, recommend, validate, verify, or warrant, either expressly or impliedly, any products, services, information, offers, promotions, claims, opinions, or content advertised, displayed, promoted, or otherwise made available on or through the marketplace platform, including, but not limited to, advertisements served through google adsense or other third-party advertising networks. The marketplace further explicitly disclaims any and all responsibility and liability for the substance, content, accuracy, completeness, legality, authenticity, safety, or reliability of any advertisements, promotional materials, or sponsored content displayed on the marketplace, or for any and all claims, representations, or guarantees made, asserted, or implied by advertisers, sponsors, or providers of promotional content. Your interactions, transactions, and engagements with any advertisers or sponsors whose advertising content is displayed on the marketplace are solely and exclusively between you and the applicable advertiser or sponsor, and you explicitly acknowledge and agree that you assume any and all risks associated with such interactions, transactions, and engagements.</p><h3><strong>9.4. Modification of Advertising Policy</strong></h3><p>The Marketplace explicitly reserves, and shall at all times retain, the unilateral, absolute, unfettered, discretionary, and non-reviewable right to comprehensively modify, unilaterally alter, arbitrarily adjust, substantially curtail, completely suspend, or permanently terminate the Advertising Policy, the advertising revenue sharing program, and any and all other aspects of advertising, promotion, and monetization on the Marketplace platform, in whole or in part, at any time, for any reason, or for no reason whatsoever, with or without prior notice, explanation, or justification, and without incurring any liability or obligation of any kind or nature whatsoever to content authors, users, advertisers, sponsors, or any other party.</p>',

