es, in accordance with applicable legal and regulatory requirements, industry best practices, and internal data governance policies. Such records of user consent may include, but are not limited to, electronic timestamps, internet protocol (IP) addresses, user account identifiers, specific version numbers or revision dates of the Terms and Conditions accepted, and any and all other relevant data points or metadata elements that may be reasonably necessary or advisable to definitively and verifiably demonstrate, document, and legally substantiate the fact, date, time, and unequivocal nature of each user’s informed, voluntary, and legally binding consent to these Terms and Conditions.</p>',

      'paragraph-14' => '<h2><strong>14. Age Restrictions</strong></h2><h3><strong>14.1. Minimum Age Requirement</strong></h3><p>Access to and utilization of the TrekGuider Marketplace is strictly and expressly restricted to users who have attained at least the minimum legally required age of contractual capacity and legal competence in their respective jurisdiction of residence. Unless explicitly and unambiguously mandated by applicable mandatory law in your jurisdiction of residence, users must be at least thirteen (13) years of age or older to lawfully access, utilize, or participate in any aspect of the Marketplace, including, but not limited to, browsing the website, registering a user account, purchasing products or services, or contributing user-generated content. Notwithstanding the foregoing general minimum age requirement of thirteen (13) years, users who are resident in jurisdictions where applicable local, state, provincial, regional, or national law, statute, ordinance, regulation, or administrative rule mandates a higher minimum age of contractual capacity or legal competence for online service utilization or digital commerce transactions, including, by way of example and without limitation, certain jurisdictions that mandate a minimum age of eighteen (18) years for such activities, must, without exception, fully and scrupulously comply with such higher locally applicable minimum age requirements, and access to or utilization of the Marketplace by any user who has not yet attained such locally mandated higher minimum age is strictly, absolutely, and unequivocally prohibited, irrespective of the user\'s physical location or place of access. By accessing or using the Marketplace in any manner, you affirmatively, unequivocally, and perpetually represent, warrant, and covenant that you fully satisfy and perpetually comply with all applicable minimum age requirements and age-based legal restrictions in your jurisdiction of residence, and that you possess the requisite legal capacity, competence, and authority to enter into and be legally bound by these Terms and Conditions.</p><h3><strong>14.2. Parental or Guardian Consent</strong></h3><p>If you are accessing or using the Marketplace, or seeking to register a user account on the Marketplace, and you have not yet attained the age of eighteen (18) years (or the locally applicable age of majority, legal adulthood, or contractual capacity in your jurisdiction of residence, if such age is greater than eighteen (18) years), you are explicitly and affirmatively required to secure, obtain, and maintain, at all times, the express, informed, verifiable, and legally valid consent, permission, and affirmative authorization of your legally recognized parent or duly appointed legal guardian to access and utilize the Marketplace, and to affirmatively accept and agree to be legally bound by these Terms and Conditions. Furthermore, in such instances, your legally recognized parent or duly appointed legal guardian must, in addition to providing verifiable consent for your access and utilization of the Marketplace, explicitly, knowingly, voluntarily, and affirmatively agree to be personally, directly, and jointly and severally liable, responsible, and legally bound by these Terms and Conditions, in their own individual legal capacity, and to fully and unconditionally guarantee your due and complete performance of all obligations, duties, and responsibilities incumbent upon you under these Terms and Conditions. The Marketplace explicitly reserves the right, exercisable in its sole and absolute discretion, to implement reasonable and legally permissible verification procedures to authenticate and validate the veracity, voluntariness, and informed nature of parental or guardian consent, and to refuse, suspend, or terminate access to the Marketplace for any user for whom verifiable and legally sufficient parental or guardian consent cannot be conclusively and affirmatively established to the Marketplace’s sole and exclusive satisfaction.</p>',

      'paragraph-15' => '<h2><strong>15. Termination of Access</strong></h2><h3><strong>15.1. Termination by the Marketplace</strong></h3><p>The Marketplace explicitly reserves, and shall at all times retain, the unilateral, absolute, unfettered, discretionary, and non-reviewable right, exercisable in its sole and exclusive judgment, to immediately, temporarily, or permanently suspend, limit, restrict, revoke, or comprehensively terminate your access to the Marketplace, your user account, and any and all features, functionalities, services, content, and benefits associated therewith, at any time, for any reason, or for no reason whatsoever, with or without prior notice, explanation, or justification to you, and without incurring any liability or obligation of any kind or nature whatsoever to you or any third party. Grounds, reasons, or justifications for such discretionary account suspension, limitation, restriction, revocation, or termination may include, but are not limited to, any actual, alleged, or suspected violation or breach of these Terms and Conditions, any applicable Marketplace policies, or any applicable law or regulation, engagement in any activities that the Marketplace, in its sole and exclusive judgment, deems to be fraudulent, deceptive, unethical, harmful, unlawful, or otherwise objectionable or detrimental to the Marketplace, its users, or its community, or any other actions, omissions, or circumstances that the Marketplace, in its sole and exclusive discretion, deems to warrant or justify account suspension or termination.</p><h3><strong>15.2. User-Initiated Termination</strong></h3><p>You, as a user, are unilaterally and unconditionally entitled to voluntarily terminate your user account on the Marketplace at any time, for any reason, or for no reason whatsoever, by affirmatively initiating account termination procedures through the designated account settings or functionalities provided on the Marketplace platform, or by directly contacting Ma