d TrekGuider Inc. and to fully bind and obligate you, perpetually and without limitation in time, to the full extent legally permissible and contractually enforceable under applicable mandatory law. By way of example and without limitation, such surviving Sections explicitly include: Section 4 (Limitation of Liability), Section 4.3 (Indemnification), Section 11 (Governing Law and Jurisdiction), Section 11.3 (Waiver of Jury Trial), Section 17 (Language and Interpretation), this Section 15.3 (Survival of Terms), Section 16 (Force Majeure), Section 18 (Miscellaneous Provisions), and any and all other provisions, clauses, and sections of these Terms and Conditions that are reasonably necessary or advisable to ensure the complete, effective, and legally enforceable preservation and protection of the Marketplace’s rights, remedies, interests, and legal entitlements following any termination or expiration of these Terms and Conditions or user account closure.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Marketplace Disclaimer Regarding Termination:</strong> The Marketplace, TrekGuider Inc., its affiliates, officers, directors, employees, agents, and representatives, explicitly disclaim any and all liability, responsibility, or legal culpability to you or any third party for any termination, suspension, limitation, or restriction of your access to the Marketplace, your user account, or any associated features, functionalities, services, or content, regardless of the cause, justification, or circumstances of such termination, suspension, limitation, or restriction, and you explicitly, knowingly, voluntarily, and irrevocably acknowledge, understand, and agree that the Marketplace shall have no obligation to provide you with any compensation, remuneration, damages, refunds, or other forms of monetary or equitable relief or consideration as a direct or indirect result of, or in connection with, any such termination, suspension, limitation, or restriction of your access to the Marketplace or your user account, except as may be expressly, unambiguously, and affirmatively mandated by applicable mandatory law, which shall be narrowly and strictly construed.</p>',

      'paragraph-16' => '<h2><strong>16. Force Majeure</strong></h2><h3><strong>16.1. Exemption from Liability</strong></h3><p>TrekGuider Inc., the Marketplace, its affiliates, subsidiaries, parent companies, successors, assigns, officers, directors, employees, agents, and representatives, shall not, under any circumstances, be held liable, responsible, or legally culpable for any failure or demonstrable delay in the due, timely, complete, or proper performance of any of its obligations, duties, responsibilities, or covenants under these Terms and Conditions, or for any losses, damages, liabilities, costs, or expenses of any kind or nature whatsoever directly or indirectly incurred by any user or third party, if such failure or delay is proximately caused by, directly arises from, or is demonstrably attributable to the occurrence or material exacerbation of events, circumstances, or causes that are unequivocally and comprehensively beyond its reasonable control, and which could not have been reasonably foreseen, anticipated, prevented, avoided, or mitigated through the exercise of commercially reasonable diligence, proactive risk management, and adherence to industry best practices (collectively, "Force Majeure Events"). Such Force Majeure Events may include, by way of example and without limitation, acts of God, natural disasters, pandemics, epidemics, public health emergencies, quarantine restrictions, governmental actions, decrees, regulations, or restrictions, acts of terrorism, civil unrest, labor strikes, industrial actions, utility failures, electrical outages, telecommunications disruptions, internet service provider failures, denial-of-service attacks, distributed denial-of-service attacks, cyberattacks, ransomware incidents, malware infections, data security breaches, acts of war, armed conflict, military hostilities, invasions, civil commotions, riots, insurrections, revolutions, embargoes, blockades, trade sanctions, economic sanctions, currency controls