  public function getCopyrightPolicy()
  {
    return [
      'header' => '<p>Copyright Policy<br><strong>Last Updated: 02\05\2025</strong></p>',

      'paragraph-1' => '<h2><strong>1. Introduction</strong></h2><h3><strong>1.1. Purpose of the Policy</strong></h3><p>This Copyright Policy ("Policy") aims to protect the intellectual property rights of content creators, authors, and third parties while ensuring compliance with the Digital Millennium Copyright Act (DMCA) and other applicable laws. It outlines the procedures for handling copyright infringement claims on the TrekGuider Inc. digital marketplace ("Marketplace").</p><h3><strong>1.2. Scope and Applicability</strong></h3><p>This Policy applies to all users, including sellers, content creators, and entities uploading or publishing content. It covers:</p><ul><li>Users’ rights and responsibilities concerning uploaded digital content.</li><li>The procedures for filing copyright infringement notices.</li><li>The process for handling counter-notifications and resolving copyright-related disputes.</li></ul><p><br></p>',

      'paragraph-2' => '<h2><strong>2. Copyright Ownership and Content Standards</strong></h2><h3><strong>2.1. User Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Original Content:</strong> Users must only upload or publish content they own or have legally acquired the rights to use.</li><li><strong>Accuracy of Representations:</strong> Users must provide truthful and complete information regarding content ownership.</li><li><strong>Prohibited Content:</strong> Users may not upload content that infringes third-party copyrights or other intellectual property rights.</li></ul><h3><strong>2.2. Marketplace Rights</strong></h3><ul><li>License Grant: By uploading content, users grant TrekGuider Inc. a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free license to use, display, reproduce, and distribute the content for the operation and promotion of the Marketplace for the duration the content is available on the platform and for a reasonable period thereafter for archival or marketing purposes related to the content\'s time on the platform.</li><li>Content Removal: TrekGuider Inc. reserves the right to remove any infringing content without prior notice if it violates this Policy.</li></ul>',

      'paragraph-3' => '<h2><strong>3. DMCA Takedown Procedures</strong></h2><h3><strong>3.1. Notice of Infringement</strong></h3><p>If you believe that content on the Marketplace infringes your copyright, you may submit a DMCA Notice to our designated Copyright Agent. Your Notice must be a written communication that includes substantially the following:<br>1. <strong>Your physical or electronic signature.</strong><br>2. <strong>Identification of the copyrighted work claimed to be infringed.</strong> <em>For example, a description of your copyrighted work, the title of a book, the name of a song, the URL of a webpage where your work is published, or a copyright registration number.</em><br>3. <strong>Identification of the infringing content, including sufficient information to locate it on the Marketplace.</strong> <em>For example, a URL or a detailed description of where the allegedly infringing material is located on the Marketplace, enabling us to find it.</em><br>4. <strong>A good faith statement that you have a good faith belief that use of the material in the manner complained of is not authorized</strong> by the copyright owner, its agent, or the law.<br>5. <strong>Your contact information,</strong> such as your address, telephone number, and email address.<br>6. <strong>A statement under penalty of perjury</strong> that the information in the notification is accurate and that you are authorized to act on behalf of the owner of an exclusive right that is allegedly infringed. You acknowledge that under 17 U.S.C. § 512(f), any person who knowingly materially misrepresents that material or activity is infringing may be subject to liability for damages.</p><h3><strong>3.2. Submission Process</strong></h3><p>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Preferred Method: Online Form:</strong> If available, users are encouraged to submit a Notice via the designated DMCA form on the Marketplace website.<br>·&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>Alternative Method: Email:</strong> As an alternative, you may send the DMCA Notice to: copyright@trekguider.com</p><h3><strong>3.3. Response to DMCA Notice</strong></h3><p>Upon receiving a valid DMCA Notice:</p><ul><li>The Marketplace reviews the claim and removes or disables access to the allegedly infringing material. The user who uploaded the content is notified of the removal and provided a copy of the DMCA Notice.</li><li>The user is notified of the removal and provided a copy of the DMCA Notice.</li></ul>',

      'paragraph-4' => '<h2><strong>4. Counter-Notification Procedures</strong></h2><h3><strong>4.1. Filing a Counter-Notification</strong></h3><p>If your content was removed due to a DMCA Notice and you believe it was removed in error, you may submit a Counter-Notification, which must be a written communication that includes substantially the following:<br>1. Your physical or electronic signature.<br>2. Identification of the content that has been removed or to which access has been disabled and the location at which the content appeared before it was removed or access to it was disabled.<br>3. A statement under penalty of perjury that you have a good faith belief that the content was removed or disabled as a result of mistake or misidentification of the content to be removed or disabled.<br>4. Your name, address, and telephone number.<br>5. A statement that you consent to the jurisdiction of the Federal District Court for the judicial district in which your address is located, or if your address is outside of the United States, for any judicial district in which TrekGuider Inc. may be found, and that you will accept service of process from the person who provided notification under subsection (c)(1)(C) or an agent of such person. You acknowledge that under 17 U.S.C. § 512(f), any person who knowingly materially misrepresents that material or activity was removed or disabled through mistake or misidentification may be subject to liability for damages.</p><h3><strong>4.2. Marketplace Review of Counter-Notification</strong></h3><ul><li>The Marketplace forwards the Counter-Notification to the original complainant.</li><li>If the complainant does not file a lawsuit within 14 business days, the removed content may be restored.</li></ul>',

      'paragraph-5' => '<h2><strong>5. Repeat Infringer Policy &amp; Safe Harbor</strong></h2><h3><strong>5.1. Repeat Infringer Policy</strong></h3><ul><li>TrekGuider Inc. may terminate accounts<strong> </strong>of users who are subject to<strong> </strong>multiple valid DMCA Notices<strong>.</strong></li></ul><h3><strong>5.2. Safe Harbor Provisions</strong></h3><ul><li>The Marketplace qualifies as a service provider under the Digital Millennium Copyright Act and seeks to benefit from the safe harbor provisions, which limit its liability for copyright infringement by users, provided that it adheres to the DMCA requirements. TrekGuider Inc. is committed to complying with the DMCA, including, but not limited to, designating a Copyright Agent to receive notifications of claimed infringement, implementing a policy to address repeat infringers, and following the notice and takedown procedures as outlined in the DMCA. By adhering to these procedures, the Marketplace aims to maintain its eligibility for the DMCA safe harbors. Users acknowledge and agree that the Marketplace acts as a passive intermediary and, to the fullest extent permitted by law, shall not be held liable for copyright infringement committed by users of the Marketplace. Sellers and content providers are solely responsible for ensuring that their content does not infringe upon the copyrights of others. However, users acknowledge that while the Marketplace strives to maintain its eligibility for DMCA safe harbors, such eligibility is not guaranteed and may be subject to change based on evolving legal interpretations and compliance requirements.</li></ul>',

      'paragraph-6' => '<h2><strong>6. Liability and Disclaimers</strong></h2><h3><strong>6.1. Limitation of Liability</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Users are solely responsible</strong> for the content they upload.</li><li>TrekGuider Inc. disclaims liability<strong> </strong>for<strong> </strong>indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from user content.</li></ul><h3><strong>6.2. No Warranties</strong></h3><ul><li>The Marketplace provides content "as is" without any warranty regarding non-infringement of third-party rights.</li></ul>',

